## 🖥️ SECTION 3: BACKEND PLACEMENT MAP (Node.js)

Every piece of backend architecture has exactly one correct home.

| What you are building | Where it belongs |
| :--- | :--- |
| **API Endpoints** | `routes/{domain}.js`. Route handlers MUST NOT contain complex business logic. They do three things: Validate -> Call Service -> Respond. |
| **Request Validation** | `middleware/validate.js` or directly before Service invocation. |
| **Authentication Logic** | `middleware/index.js` -> `authenticateJWT`. |
| **Business Logic** | `services/{domain}.service.js`. All queries, calculations, and mutations live here. |
| **Database Queries** | `services/{domain}.service.js`. Always use parameterized array inputs (`[val1, val2]`). NEVER interpolate user input into SQL strings. |
| **Configuration Values** | `config/loader.js` (reading from `.json` files). Rates, delays, limits, and radii are never hardcoded. |
| **Scheduled Jobs / Cron** | `services/cron.service.js`. |
| **Idempotency Locks** | `config/redis.js` or directly via MySQL `FOR UPDATE` in transactional queries. |

