## 🗄️ SECTION 4: DATA OWNERSHIP MAP

When you need data, retrieve it from its absolute Source of Truth.

| Data Type | Absolute Owner & Source of Truth |
| :--- | :--- |
| **User Identity & Role** | MySQL: `users` table. Mobile checks `authStore`. |
| **Session State** | Mobile: `expo-secure-store` (JWT). |
| **Job Statuses** | MySQL: `jobs.status`. Mirrored to Firebase `active_jobs/{jobId}/status` for UI. |
| **Job OTPs** | MySQL: `start_otp_hash` & `end_otp_hash`. NEVER written to Firebase. NEVER validated on the mobile client. |
| **Worker Live Location** | MySQL: `worker_profiles.last_location_lat/lng`. Mirrored to Firebase `worker_presence/{id}`. |
| **Invoice / Pricing** | MySQL: `job_invoices` table. Mobile receives via `/api/jobs/estimate` or `/api/payment/invoice`. |
| **Chat Messages** | MySQL: `messages` table. Firebase handles ONLY typing states and unread counts natively. |
| **Feature Flags** | Server: `features.config.json`. |

